records.addlTxt:
Defendant Joshua J Schwab in court with attorney Bruce J Rosen.  Michele W. Hulgaard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed outright.  Count #3 is dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Defendants mother makes statements. Attorney Rosen makes statements.  Defendant makes statements. 
The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of: Count #1.  
36 months of Imprisonment (Credit - 1 day )
18 months of Initial Confinement
18 months of Extended Supervision
Term of Probation: 3 Years, may be transferred to Dane County
Early release after two years if agent deems appropriate
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances;
No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Disclose to any physician in writing your drug history/dependency signed by your physician and provide a copy to your Agent. 
Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
Condition Time: 60 days Huber with work and treatment,  NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - To commence 1/8/2016 @ 5:00 pm.  Last 30 days STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
FINE:  $505.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $250.00  to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
